text: hi everyone the Blackberry Corporation
here the internet's busiest music nerd
and it's time for a review of this new
ketramine album
from kaytranada and amine this is the
new highly anticipated collab album
between Portland rapper amine and
Haitian Canadian music producer
kaytranada both of whom had mid-2010
breakouts that ran along very different
trajectories while amine has had quite a
bit of mainstream success to this day
there's still sort of a low-key
underground Stoner rap demeanor about
him with lots of laid back slick and
clever Rhymes that don't sound like
they're desperate for anyone's attention
but still kind of hit and are worth
replaying meanwhile kaytranada is
handily one of the most versatile
hip-hop adjacent producers out there
today so versatile his work is often
hard to categorize as any one thing with
a lot of Dance Fusion Styles being
worked into the grooves of his Beats I
mean his breakout record 99.9 was
released on Excel records if that tells
you anything and landed features not
only from the likes of fonte and Vic
Mensa but this record also made space
for dance and pop Act such as little
dragon as well as Aluna George so
honestly in theory this potentially is a
hot little collaboration that we have
here not only because amine's energy
will most likely match the Loki Vibe of
catronado's Beats there's even a line on
this record of amine saying that he
asked him for some free beats back in
2015 but amine also tends to thrive on
production that is at least a little
left field or unusual so again that's
kaytranada this thing should be fire but
it's not it's just okay which is
unfortunate because listening to this
thing it's really one of those records
that you know could have been a lot
better especially if the Deep Cuts were
going as hard as the singles and the
highlights because as it currently
stands this ketramina project is a
little scant at 33 minutes of run time
and it's really the singles and the
feature cuts that pack the most punch be
that forever with L which is a vaguely
tropical Bop with bump and keys and some
hooky vocal chops from Williams amine's
bars are consistently funny and flirty
whether he is spitting lines about [ __ ]
percussion or Stacy Dash's garbage
political takes not exactly lyrically
focused or anything like that but the
track overall is blissful and feel good
with less talk about it we have more
head-notting beats dreamy keys and
smooth flows from amine that are so
understated he makes it all sound
effortless even when his rhyme schemes
and rhythms are getting pretty tight
however Freddie Gibbs goes even harder
in the second half of the track kind of
stealing the show which also happens on
the song Master P featuring Big Sean
where kaytranada's production also
carries with simple and crispy snares
and hi-hats sitting at the center of
this Whirlwind made of reverse
descending Melodies and like these
really ghostly androgynous vocal leads
which makes me wish more of the Beats on
this thing were this colorful and out
there because truth be told some of the
production on this project came across
more skeletal and underwhelming Half
Baked than I thought it would to the
point where it really takes the wind out
of the song sails be it on the opener
who he is which sets an inadvertently
sleepy tone for the entire project which
is perplexing given that the opening
vocal snippet that kicks the entire
record off would lead you to think you
were going to hear like amine and
ketronata just go in just hit us with an
explosion right off the bat but that
could not be further from uh the actual
results that we see there's also west
side which features a very pretty nice
distant little string sample throughout
the track but the beat itself is one of
the stiffest and driest on the entire
record and amine didn't exactly use this
extra space to fill this vacuum with
super standout bars or anything I mean
the bust out the troops line if you want
to look into that one is kind of
hilarious but outside of that we have
some weak similes to Sister Sister and
Sex in the City rebuke I thought was a
snoozer of a song interlude on the
project and we also have Ulster up which
is maybe the most annoying song on the
entire thing with a very sour two chord
progression playing throughout much of
the track and a beat that is so tense I
just can't really vibe to it at all it
makes me feel like I'm sitting in a
Brazilian dentist office waiting for a
root canal however stfu3 is one of the
few moments on this thing that is so
low-key but also stand out and eccentric
the song sounds like what you would get
if Pharrell and clips had to assemble a
track for the Twilight Zone it's got
kooky Bassy minimal production meanwhile
amine brings nothing but Charisma for
two solid verses
has some funny bars and out of breath
refrains throughout the track that are
kind of cool even if the pacing of the
track is a little tedious and didn't
need to be this long then the closing
moments of the record I just didn't
really think were that interesting k a
longest track here by a mile but kind of
finishes the record off as
unceremoniously as it starts In fairness
the beat is relatively mesmerizing and
we do get some self-affirming food for
thought from amine in the verses but in
practice the whole thing is really just
this big dreamy diatribe with no real
point or sense of direction really an
unearned Victory lap and then there's a
kind of bold beat switch in the last leg
of the song that doesn't even really fit
the rest of the track in tone it just
feels super tacked on overall I guess
I'll say that on this project there are
some moments that are fireworks then
there are others where either kaytranada
or mene are playing it just a little too
easy going and as a result the bars or
vice versa the beat kind of carry not to
mention Amina is usually outshined by
the guest features on this thing pretty
handily even on I featuring Snoop Dogg
even though uh what Snoop hands in is
pretty standard as far as his features
go these days but yeah this record it's
okay it's really the singles and the
featured tracks that uh stand out the
furthest hit the hardest and make the
record what it is much of everything
else is either okay or just comes across
like mild filler feeling a strong five
